name: 3-bromo-4-cyanopyridine

The nitrogen in the pyridine ring increases the melting point due to the contribution of the lone pair of electrons on nitrogen that participate in resonance, which stabilizes the structure and increases the melting point by about 25 degrees Celsius. The bromo functional group will add some mass and size to the molecule, leading to higher van der Waals forces and increasing the melting point by approximately 15 degrees Celsius. The cyano group adds polarity to the molecule because of the carbon-nitrogen triple bond, and this can additionally raise the melting point by another 20 degrees Celsius due to increased dipole-dipole interactions.
